ities and constraints facing a small, devolved nation. After years of debate on what powers Scotland should have, this book examines how they might be used to shape the country’s future.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 4aPolitics. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Social Services & Welfare.2bisacsh1 aBell, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCairney, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDenny, Emily St., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEiser, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarvey, Malcolm, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKeating, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLecca, Patrizio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLisenkova, Katerina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLiñeira, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcAngus, Craig, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcEwen, Nicola, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcGregor, Peter G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRummery, Kirstein, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSwales, Kim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311078140340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781474416443zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781474416443423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781474416443/original  a978-3-11-078140-3  Edinb